#. <section class="sutta" id="sn53.1-12"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn53.1-12:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 53"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 53"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn53.1-12:0.2"
msgid "1. Gaṅgāpeyyālavagga"
msgstr "1. Abbreviated Texts on the Ganges"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 1–​12. Jhānādisutta → pathamasuddhiyaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "sn53.1-12:0.3"
msgid "1–​12. Jhānādisutta"
msgstr "1–12. Absorptions, Etc."

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.307"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn53.1-12:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn53.1-12:1.2"
msgid "Tatra kho … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn53.1-12:1.3"
msgid "“cattārome, bhikkhave, jhānā."
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these four absorptions."

msgctxt "sn53.1-12:1.4"
msgid "Katame cattāro?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "sn53.1-12:1.5"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi "
"savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja "
"viharati."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from "
"unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has "
"the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping "
"it connected."

msgctxt "sn53.1-12:1.6"
msgid ""
"Vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ "
"avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"As the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, they enter "
"and remain in the second absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of "
"immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified mind, without "
"placing the mind and keeping it connected."

msgctxt "sn53.1-12:1.7"
msgid ""
"Pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca viharati sato ca sampajāno sukhañca kāyena "
"paṭisaṃvedeti, yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti: ‘upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī’ti "
"tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"And with the fading away of rapture, they enter and remain in the third "
"absorption, where they meditate with equanimity, mindful and aware, "
"personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, ‘"
"Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss.’"

msgctxt "sn53.1-12:1.8"
msgid ""
"Sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ "
"atthaṅgamā adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ "
"upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and sadness, they "
"enter and remain in the fourth absorption, without pleasure or pain, with "
"pure equanimity and mindfulness."

msgctxt "sn53.1-12:1.9"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro jhānāti."
msgstr "These are the four absorptions."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.308"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn53.1-12:2.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, gaṅgā nadī pācīnaninnā pācīnapoṇā pācīnapabbhārā;"
msgstr "The Ganges river slants, slopes, and inclines to the east."

msgctxt "sn53.1-12:2.2"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cattāro jhāne bhāvento cattāro jhāne "
"bahulīkaronto nibbānaninno hoti nibbānapoṇo nibbānapabbhāro."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, a mendicant who develops and cultivates the four "
"absorptions slants, slopes, and inclines to extinguishment."

msgctxt "sn53.1-12:2.3"
msgid ""
"Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cattāro jhāne bhāvento cattāro jhāne "
"bahulīkaronto nibbānaninno hoti nibbānapoṇo nibbānapabbhāro?"
msgstr ""
"And how does a mendicant who develops and cultivates the four absorptions "
"slant, slope, and incline to extinguishment?"

msgctxt "sn53.1-12:2.4"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi "
"savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja "
"viharati."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from "
"unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has "
"the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping "
"it connected."

msgctxt "sn53.1-12:2.5"
msgid "Vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā … pe … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ …"
msgstr ""
"As the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, they enter "
"and remain in the second absorption …"

msgctxt "sn53.1-12:2.6"
msgid "tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ …"
msgstr "third absorption …"

msgctxt "sn53.1-12:2.7"
msgid "catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr "fourth absorption."

msgctxt "sn53.1-12:2.8"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cattāro jhāne bhāvento cattāro jhāne "
"bahulīkaronto nibbānaninno hoti nibbānapoṇo nibbānapabbhāro”ti."
msgstr ""
"That’s how a mendicant who develops and cultivates the four absorptions "
"slants, slopes, and inclines to extinguishment.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn53.1-12:2.9"
msgid "Dvādasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn53.1-12:2.10"
msgid "Gaṅgāpeyyālavaggo paṭhamo."
msgstr "(To be expanded for each of the different rivers as in SN 45.91–102.)"

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn53.1-12:3.1"
msgid "Cha pācīnato ninnā,"
msgstr "Six on slanting to the east,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn53.1-12:3.2"
msgid "cha ninnā ca samuddato;"
msgstr "and six on slanting to the ocean;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn53.1-12:3.3"
msgid "Dvete cha dvādasa honti,"
msgstr "these two sixes make twelve,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn53.1-12:3.4"
msgid "vaggo tena pavuccatīti."
msgstr "and that’s how this chapter is recited."
